<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="42" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 Struma Valley/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-28T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 28,
                                        1928—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>27. Your 32 April 26, 7 p.m. Department has obtained statement of
                            ownership of stock of Foundation Company (Foreign) on the basis of which
                            it authorizes you to answer in the affirmative.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
